column12:
What Am I Looking At?
'Soft' scores are the two subcategories of switch scoring that focus on the extrinsic, non-physical characteristics that make switches more or less valuable. The 'Context' and 'Other' categories comprise 30 of the 100 points in this switch scoring system and are based on consideration of, but not limited to, availability, pricing, accessibility, legacy, community awareness, vendor and manufacturer support, etc. 
Since the 'time decay' function discussed in the Overall Total tab is correcting for a bias in contextual relevancy shift, it is also applied to the scores in this tab as well.
